<TEI xmlns="http://www.tei-c.org/ns/1.0" xmlns:frus="http://history.state.gov/frus/ns/1.0"><text><body><div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1872-02-22T23:59:59-05:00" frus:doc-dateTime-min="1872-02-22T00:00:00-05:00" n="352" subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d352">
                        <head>No. 352.<lb/><hi rend="italic">Mr. <persName type="from">Fish</persName> to Mr. <persName type="to">Riotte</persName>.</hi></head>
                        <opener>
                            <dateline rendition="#right"><placeName><hi rend="smallcaps">Department
                                        of State</hi>,<lb/><hi rend="italic">Washington</hi></placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1872-02-22"><hi rend="italic">February</hi> 22,
                                    1872</date>.</dateline>
                            <seg rendition="#left">No. 68.]</seg>
                        </opener>
                        <p><hi rend="smallcaps">Sir</hi>. Referring to your dispatch No. 97, of the
                            21st ultimo, on the subject of the exploration of the Nicaraguan
                            Isthmus, with a view to the construction of an interoceanic canal, I
                            have to inform you that an expedition for that purpose has been ordered
                            by this Government, and that a vessel may be expected in Nicaragua in a
                            few weeks, to begin the survey. I take this occasion to acknowledge the
                            receipt of your dispatch No. 96, of the 11th ultimo.</p>
                        <p>I am, &amp;c,</p>
                        <closer>
                            <signed>HAMILTON FISH.</signed>
                        </closer>
                    </div>
                    </body></text></TEI>